A student wants to check if a number is even. Their code always prints "odd" for the number 4. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
int main()
{
    int n = 4;
    if (n / 2 == 0)
        std::cout << "even\n";
    else
        std::cout << "odd\n";
    return 0;
}
```
